fields.title: The Shawshank Redemption
fields.overview: Two imprisoned men bond over a number of years, finding solace and eventual redemption through acts of common decency.

fields.title: The Godfather
fields.overview: An organized crime dynasty's aging patriarch transfers control of his clandestine empire to his reluctant son.

fields.title: The Dark Knight
fields.overview: When the menace known as the Joker wreaks havoc and chaos on the people of Gotham, Batman must accept one of the greatest psychological and physical tests of his ability to fight injustice.

fields.title: The Godfather: Part II
fields.overview: The early life and career of Vito Corleone in 1920s New York City is portrayed, while his son, Michael, expands and tightens his grip on the family crime syndicate.

fields.title: 12 Angry Men
fields.overview: A jury holdout attempts to prevent a miscarriage of justice by forcing his colleagues to reconsider the evidence.

fields.title: The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King
fields.overview: Gandalf and Aragorn lead the World of Men against Sauron's army to draw his gaze from Frodo and Sam as they approach Mount Doom with the One Ring.

fields.title: Pulp Fiction
fields.overview: The lives of two mob hitmen, a boxer, a gangster and his wife, and a pair of diner bandits intertwine in four tales of violence and redemption.

fields.title: Schindler's List
fields.overview: In German-occupied Poland during World War II, industrialist Oskar Schindler gradually becomes concerned for his Jewish workforce after witnessing their persecution by the Nazis.

fields.title: Inception
fields.overview: A thief who steals corporate secrets through the use of dream-sharing technology is given the inverse task of planting an idea into the mind of a C.E.O.

fields.title: Fight Club
fields.overview: An insomniac office worker and a devil-may-care soapmaker form an underground fight club that evolves into something much, much more.

fields.title: The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring
fields.overview: A meek Hobbit from the Shire and eight companions set out on a journey to destroy the powerful One Ring and save Middle-earth from the Dark Lord Sauron.

fields.title: Forrest Gump
fields.overview: The presidencies of Kennedy and Johnson, the events of Vietnam, Watergate and other historical events unfold through the perspective of an Alabama man with an IQ of 75, whose only desire is to be reunited with his childhood sweetheart.

fields.title: The Good, The Bad and The Ugly
fields.overview: A bounty hunting scam joins two men in an uneasy alliance against a third in a race to find a fortune in gold buried in a remote cemetery.

fields.title: The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers
fields.overview: While Frodo and Sam edge closer to Mordor with the help of the shifty Gollum, the divided fellowship makes a stand against Sauron's new ally, Saruman, and his hordes of Isengard.

fields.title: The Matrix
fields.overview: When a beautiful stranger leads computer hacker Neo to a forbidding underworld, he discovers the shocking truth--the life he knows is the elaborate deception of an evil cyber-intelligence.

fields.title: Goodfellas
fields.overview: The story of Henry Hill and his life in the mob, covering his relationship with his wife Karen Hill and his mob partners Jimmy Conway and Tommy DeVito in the Italian-American crime syndicate.

fields.title: Star Wars: Episode V - The Empire Strikes Back
fields.overview: After the Rebels are brutally overpowered by the Empire on the ice planet Hoth, Luke Skywalker begins Jedi training with Yoda, while his friends are pursued by Darth Vader and a bounty hunter named Boba Fett all over the galaxy.

fields.title: One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest
fields.overview: A criminal pleads insanity and is admitted to a mental institution, where he rebels against the oppressive nurse and rallies up the scared patients.

fields.title: Parasite
fields.overview: Greed and class discrimination threaten the newly formed symbiotic relationship between the wealthy Park family and the destitute Kim clan.

fields.title: Interstellar
fields.overview: A team of explorers travel through a wormhole in space in an attempt to ensure humanity's survival.

fields.title: City of God
fields.overview: In the slums of Rio, two kids' paths diverge as one struggles to become a photographer and the other a kingpin.

fields.title: Spirited Away
fields.overview: During her family's move to the suburbs, a sullen 10-year-old girl wanders into a world ruled by gods, witches, and spirits, and where humans are changed into beasts.

fields.title: Saving Private Ryan
fields.overview: Following the Normandy Landings, a group of U.S. soldiers go behind enemy lines to retrieve a paratrooper whose brothers have been killed in action.

fields.title: The Green Mile
fields.overview: The lives of guards on Death Row are affected by one of their charges: a black man accused of child murder and rape, yet who has a mysterious gift.

fields.title: Se7en
fields.overview: Two detectives, a rookie and a veteran, hunt a serial killer who uses the seven deadly sins as his motives.

fields.title: The Silence of the Lambs
fields.overview: A young F.B.I. cadet must receive the help of an incarcerated and manipulative cannibal killer to help catch another serial killer, a madman who skins his victims.

fields.title: Star Wars: Episode IV - A New Hope
fields.overview: Luke Skywalker joins forces with a Jedi Knight, a cocky pilot, a Wookiee and two droids to save the galaxy from the Empire's world-destroying battle station, while also attempting to rescue Princess Leia from the mysterious Darth Vader.

fields.title: Seven Samurai
fields.overview: A poor village under attack by bandits recruits seven unemployed samurai to help them defend themselves.

fields.title: Joker
fields.overview: In Gotham City, mentally troubled comedian Arthur Fleck is disregarded and mistreated by society. He then embarks on a downward spiral of revolution and bloody crime. This path brings him face-to-face with his alter-ego: the Joker.

fields.title: Whiplash
fields.overview: A promising young drummer enrolls at a cut-throat music conservatory where his dreams of greatness are mentored by an instructor who will stop at nothing to realize a student's potential.

fields.title: The Intouchables
fields.overview: After he becomes a quadriplegic from a paragliding accident, an aristocrat hires a young man from the projects to be his caregiver.

fields.title: The Prestige
fields.overview: After a tragic accident, two stage magicians engage in a battle to create the ultimate illusion while sacrificing everything they have to outwit each other.

fields.title: The Departed
fields.overview: An undercover cop and a mole in the police attempt to identify each other while infiltrating an Irish gang in South Boston.

fields.title: The Pianist
fields.overview: A Polish Jewish musician struggles to survive the destruction of the Warsaw ghetto of World War II.

fields.title: Gladiator
fields.overview: A former Roman General sets out to exact vengeance against the corrupt emperor who murdered his family and sent him into slavery.

fields.title: American History X
fields.overview: A former neo-nazi skinhead tries to prevent his younger brother from going down the same wrong path that he did.

fields.title: The Usual Suspects
fields.overview: A sole survivor tells of the twisty events leading up to a horrific gun battle on a boat, which began when five criminals met at a seemingly random police lineup.

fields.title: The Lion King
fields.overview: Lion prince Simba and his father are targeted by his bitter uncle, who wants to ascend the throne himself.

fields.title: Terminator 2: Judgment Day
fields.overview: A cyborg, identical to the one who failed to kill Sarah Connor, must now protect her teenage son, John Connor, from a more advanced and powerful cyborg.

fields.title: Cinema Paradiso
fields.overview: A filmmaker recalls his childhood when falling in love with the pictures at the cinema of his home village and forms a deep friendship with the cinema's projectionist.

fields.title: Back to the Future
fields.overview: Marty McFly, a 17-year-old high school student, is accidentally sent thirty years into the past in a time-traveling DeLorean invented by his close friend, the eccentric scientist Doc Brown.

fields.title: Once Upon a Time in the West
fields.overview: A mysterious stranger with a harmonica joins forces with a notorious desperado to protect a beautiful widow from a ruthless assassin working for the railroad.

fields.title: Psycho
fields.overview: A Phoenix secretary embezzles $40,000 from her employer's client, goes on the run, and checks into a remote motel run by a young man under the domination of his mother.

fields.title: Casablanca
fields.overview: A cynical expatriate American cafe owner struggles to decide whether or not to help his former lover and her fugitive husband escape the Nazis in French Morocco.

fields.title: Modern Times
fields.overview: The Tramp struggles to live in modern industrial society with the help of a young homeless woman.

fields.title: Star Wars: Episode VI - Return of the Jedi
fields.overview: After a daring mission to rescue Han Solo from Jabba the Hutt, the Rebels dispatch to Endor to destroy the second Death Star. Meanwhile, Luke struggles to help Darth Vader back from the dark side without falling into the Emperor's trap.

fields.title: Your Name.
fields.overview: Two strangers find themselves linked in a bizarre way. When a connection forms, will distance be the only thing to keep them apart?

fields.title: Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse
fields.overview: Teen Miles Morales becomes the Spider-Man of his universe, and must join with five spider-powered individuals from other dimensions to stop a threat for all realities.

fields.title: Avengers: Endgame
fields.overview: After the devastating events of Avengers: Infinity War (2018), the universe is in ruins. With the help of remaining allies, the Avengers assemble once more in order to reverse Thanos' actions and restore balance to the universe.

fields.title: Avengers: Infinity War
fields.overview: The Avengers and their allies must be willing to sacrifice all in an attempt to defeat the powerful Thanos before his blitz of devastation and ruin puts an end to the universe.

fields.title: Coco
fields.overview: Aspiring musician Miguel, confronted with his family's ancestral ban on music, enters the Land of the Dead to find his great-great-grandfather, a legendary singer.

fields.title: Django Unchained
fields.overview: With the help of a German bounty hunter, a freed slave sets out to rescue his wife from a brutal Mississippi plantation owner.

fields.title: The Dark Knight Rises
fields.overview: Eight years after the Joker's reign of anarchy, Batman, with the help of the enigmatic Catwoman, is forced from his exile to save Gotham City from the brutal guerrilla terrorist Bane.

fields.title: 3 Idiots
fields.overview: Two friends are searching for their long lost companion. They revisit their college days and recall the memories of their friend who inspired them to think differently, even as the rest of the world called them "idiots".

fields.title: WALL-E
fields.overview: In the distant future, a small waste-collecting robot inadvertently embarks on a space journey that will ultimately decide the fate of mankind.

fields.title: Amadeus
fields.overview: The life, success and troubles of Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart, as told by Antonio Salieri, the contemporaneous composer who was insanely jealous of Mozart's talent and claimed to have murdered him.

fields.title: Oldboy
fields.overview: After being kidnapped and imprisoned for fifteen years, Oh Dae-Su is released, only to find that he must find his captor in five days.

fields.title: Memento
fields.overview: A man with short-term memory loss attempts to track down his wife's murderer.

fields.title: Princess Mononoke
fields.overview: On a journey to find the cure for a Tatarigami's curse, Ashitaka finds himself in the middle of a war between the forest gods and Tatara, a mining colony. In this quest he also meets San, the Mononoke Hime.

fields.title: Raiders of the Lost Ark
fields.overview: In 1936, archaeologist and adventurer Indiana Jones is hired by the U.S. government to find the Ark of the Covenant before Adolf Hitler's Nazis can obtain its awesome powers.

fields.title: The Shining
fields.overview: A family heads to an isolated hotel for the winter where a sinister presence influences the father into violence, while his psychic son sees horrific forebodings from both past and future.

fields.title: Apocalypse Now
fields.overview: A U.S. Army officer serving in Vietnam is tasked with assassinating a renegade Special Forces Colonel who sees himself as a god.

fields.title: Alien
fields.overview: After a space merchant vessel receives an unknown transmission as a distress call, one of the crew is attacked by a mysterious life form and they soon realize that its life cycle has merely begun.

fields.title: Dr. Strangelove or: How I Learned to Stop Worrying and Love the Bomb
fields.overview: An insane general triggers a path to nuclear holocaust that a War Room full of politicians and generals frantically tries to stop.

fields.title: Rear Window
fields.overview: A wheelchair-bound photographer spies on his neighbors from his apartment window and becomes convinced one of them has committed murder.

April 6th, 1917. As a regiment assembles to wage war deep in enemy territory, two soldiers are assigned to race against time and deliver a message that will stop 1,600 men from walking straight into a deadly trap.

fields.title: The Hunt
fields.overview: A teacher lives a lonely life, all the while struggling over his son's custody. His life slowly gets better as he finds love and receives good news from his son, but his new luck is about to be brutally shattered by an innocent little lie.

fields.title: A Separation
fields.overview: A married couple are faced with a difficult decision - to improve the life of their child by moving to another country or to stay in Iran and look after a deteriorating parent who has Alzheimer's disease.

fields.title: Incendies
fields.overview: Twins journey to the Middle East to discover their family history and fulfill their mother's last wishes.

fields.title: Inglourious Basterds
fields.overview: In Nazi-occupied France during World War II, a plan to assassinate Nazi leaders by a group of Jewish U.S. soldiers coincides with a theatre owner's vengeful plans for the same.

fields.title: Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind
fields.overview: When their relationship turns sour, a couple undergoes a medical procedure to have each other erased from their memories.

fields.title: Amalie
fields.overview: Amélie is an innocent and naive girl in Paris with her own sense of justice. She decides to help those around her and, along the way, discovers love.

fields.title: Snatch
fields.overview: Unscrupulous boxing promoters, violent bookmakers, a Russian gangster, incompetent amateur robbers and supposedly Jewish jewelers fight to track down a priceless stolen diamond.

fields.title: Requiem for a Dream
fields.overview: The drug-induced utopias of four Coney Island people are shattered when their addictions run deep.

fields.title: American Beauty
fields.overview: A sexually frustrated suburban father has a mid-life crisis after becoming infatuated with his daughter's best friend.
